dp:Sidecar a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Sidecar"@en ;
    owl:equivalentClass [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:intersectionOf ( dp:Component [ a owl:Restriction ;
                        owl:onClass dp:Data_Product ;
                        owl:onProperty dp:is_sidecar_for ;
                        owl:qualifiedCardinality "1"^^xsd:nonNegativeInteger ] ) ] ;
    skos:definition "A data product sidecar is a process that shares the execution context of a data product and is only responsible for domain-agnostic and cross-cutting concerns such as policy execution. In addition to policy execution, the sidecar process can be extended to implement other standardized features of a data product such as discovery. Dehghani, Zhamak. Data Mesh: Delivering Data-Driven Value at Scale (p. 4). O'Reilly Media. Kindle Edition."@en,
        "Sidecars provide a convenient architectural location for enforcing semantic constraints, turning models and validation rules into executable components attached to data products."@en ;
    dp:embedding_note """Sidecar has label Sidecar.
Sidecar has definition A data product sidecar is a process that shares the execution context of a data product and is only responsible for domain-agnostic and cross-cutting concerns such as policy execution. In addition to policy execution, the sidecar process can be extended to implement other standardized features of a data product such as discovery. Dehghani, Zhamak. Data Mesh: Delivering Data-Driven Value at Scale (p. 4). O'Reilly Media. Kindle Edition.
Sidecar has definition Sidecars provide a convenient architectural location for enforcing semantic constraints, turning models and validation rules into executable components attached to data products."""@en .

